{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FTKUMywN3gjB17DFBiKJEv","type":"tool_result","content":"   685→| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n   686→\n   687→### `cloche logs`\n   688→\n   689→```\n   690→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   691→```\n   692→\n   693→| Flag | Description |\n   694→|------|-------------|\n   695→| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   696→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   697→| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   698→\n   699→Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   700→\n   701→### `cloche poll`\n   702→\n   703→```\n   704→cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n   705→```\n   706→\n   707→Block until all specified runs finish. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 if all runs succeeded, 1 if any failed or were cancelled.\n   708→\n   709→With a single run ID, prints step-level progress. With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary (e.g. `id1: running`) and re-prints whenever a state changes. Use `cloche logs` for detailed output of individual runs.\n   710→\n   711→### `cloche stop`\n   712→\n   713→```\n   714→cloche stop <run-id>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8530080f-5bbb-4b36-9913-140e127b35d2","uuid":"70af41e0-980b-406a-84f6-5581ffcaf7aa","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n```\n\nBlock until all specified runs finish. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 if all runs succeeded, 1 if any failed or were cancelled.\n\nWith a single run ID, prints step-level progress. With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary (e.g. `id1: running`) and re-prints whenever a state changes. Use `cloche logs` for detailed output of individual runs.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>","numLines":30,"startLine":685,"totalLines":922}}}
